<p>As some point I had to generate a random MAC address. This is the snippet I used:</p>
<pre><code class="language-{.python">import random

def randomMAC():
  mac = [0x00, 0x16, 0x3e,
         random.randint(0x00, 0x7f),
         random.randint(0x00, 0xff),
         random.randint(0x00, 0xff),
  ]
  return ':'.join(map(lambda x: &quot;%02x&quot; % x, mac))

print 'MAC =&gt; %s' % randomMAC()
</code></pre>
<pre><code class="language-example">MAC =&gt; 00:16:3e:7e:f7:fa
</code></pre>
